Heath Haussamen / NMPolitics.netSUNLAND PARK, N.M. — According to the state tourism bureau, Sunland Park is one of the last towns of the Old West, tucked below the commanding peak of Mt.
In the dry, bureaucratic language of the U.S. Census Bureau, Sunland Park is simply one of the hardest-to-count tracts in the entire country.
For the first time since 1950, the Census Bureau plans to ask all households about citizenship status.
‘You can’t trust anyone’“We have certain amendments that protect us here in the United States,” Lulu Hernandez assures a recent gathering at the Sunland Park Public Library.
Sunland Park will need to boost its budget with federal funds — funds dependent on census data — to overcome those challenges.